---
import Canvas from "../layouts/Canvas.astro";
const styles = `
    .router-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(200px, 1fr)); gap: 6px; margin-top: 12px; }
    .router-chip {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 11.5px;
      padding: 6px 9px;
      background: var(--muted);
      border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
      border-radius: 4px;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
    }
    .stat-row { display: flex; gap: 24px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 12px; }
    .stat-pill {
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: var(--radius-md);
      padding: 14px 18px;
      background: var(--card);
      min-width: 160px;
    }
    .stat-pill .stat-num { font-size: 26px; font-weight: 600; font-family: var(--font-mono); }
    .stat-pill .stat-label { font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-muted); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; margin-top: 4px; }
    .middleware-stack { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; }
    .mw-row {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: center;
      padding: 12px 16px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: var(--radius-md);
      background: var(--card);
    }
    .mw-row .mw-name { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12.5px; font-weight: 500; }
    .mw-row .mw-desc { font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--text-muted); margin-left: 16px; }
    .mw-row .mw-order { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10.5px; color: var(--text-faint); margin-right: 12px; }
  `;
---

<Canvas title="04 · API Surface — Sardis Canvas" currentId="api-surface">
<Fragment slot="head">
  <style is:global set:html={styles}></style>
</Fragment>

<section class="hero">
        <span class="eyebrow">Canvas 04 · System</span>
        <h1>API Surface</h1>
        <p class="hero-lead">
          One FastAPI application, 123 routers, grouped by domain. Every router sits behind the same
          middleware stack (request-id, logging, security headers, rate limit, auth) and — for anything
          that moves money — funnels into a single <code>PaymentOrchestrator.execute()</code> chokepoint.
          This canvas is the catalogue.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="section" style="padding-top:0; border-top:0;">
        <div class="callout callout-info">
          <span class="callout-title">TL;DR</span>
          The surface is large on purpose — every money movement, policy decision, compliance check, and
          webhook callback gets its own router so the seams are explicit. The surface is also uniform on
          purpose — every request traverses the same middleware, the same principal extractor, and the same
          pre-execution pipeline. Wide catalogue, narrow spine.
        </div>
        <div class="stat-row">
          <div class="stat-pill"><div class="stat-num">123</div><div class="stat-label">Routers</div></div>
          <div class="stat-pill"><div class="stat-num">/api/v2</div><div class="stat-label">Canonical prefix</div></div>
          <div class="stat-pill"><div class="stat-num">12</div><div class="stat-label">Domain groups</div></div>
          <div class="stat-pill"><div class="stat-num">10</div><div class="stat-label">Middleware layers</div></div>
          <div class="stat-pill"><div class="stat-num">RFC 7807</div><div class="stat-label">Error model</div></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Middleware stack -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">The Spine</div>
          <h2>Middleware stack — outermost first.</h2>
          <p class="text-muted" style="max-width:720px;">
            Registered in <code>packages/reference-api/server/main.py</code>. FastAPI/Starlette
            middleware executes outermost-registered-first on request, innermost-first on response. If you
            need to add a cross-cutting concern, add it here, not in a router.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="middleware-stack">
          <div class="mw-row">
            <div><span class="mw-order">01</span><span class="mw-name">RequestIdMiddleware</span><span class="mw-desc">Assigns <code>x-request-id</code>, propagates through logs and downstream calls.</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="mw-row">
            <div><span class="mw-order">02</span><span class="mw-name">StructuredLoggingMiddleware</span><span class="mw-desc">JSON log per request: method, path, status, latency_ms, principal, request_id.</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="mw-row">
            <div><span class="mw-order">03</span><span class="mw-name">SecurityHeadersMiddleware</span><span class="mw-desc">CSP, HSTS, X-Frame-Options, Referrer-Policy, Permissions-Policy.</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="mw-row">
            <div><span class="mw-order">04</span><span class="mw-name">RequestBodyLimitMiddleware</span><span class="mw-desc">Rejects payloads over configured byte cap — defends against memory-pressure DoS.</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="mw-row">
            <div><span class="mw-order">05</span><span class="mw-name">RateLimitMiddleware</span><span class="mw-desc">Redis-backed token bucket; fail-closed in prod if Redis unreachable (<code>SARDIS_REDIS_URL</code>).</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="mw-row">
            <div><span class="mw-order">06</span><span class="mw-name">TapVerificationMiddleware</span><span class="mw-desc">Verifies Visa TAP agent identity headers (Ed25519 / ECDSA-P256) when enabled.</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="mw-row">
            <div><span class="mw-order">07</span><span class="mw-name">X402PaymentMiddleware</span><span class="mw-desc">Implements x402 Payment Required on gated endpoints; verifies on-chain settlement proof.</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="mw-row">
            <div><span class="mw-order">08</span><span class="mw-name">UsageMeteringMiddleware</span><span class="mw-desc">Records billable-event rows for Polar; tags by principal + endpoint class.</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="mw-row">
            <div><span class="mw-order">09</span><span class="mw-name">ActivityLoggerMiddleware</span><span class="mw-desc">Write-ahead of every mutating call into the audit log (feeds Canvas 20).</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="mw-row">
            <div><span class="mw-order">10</span><span class="mw-name">CORSMiddleware</span><span class="mw-desc">Canonical origins: public site origins configured by deployment + merchant <code>embed_origin</code>.</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Mermaid: request flow through middleware -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Interaction</div>
          <h2>One HTTPS request, traced through the stack.</h2>
          <p class="text-muted" style="max-width:720px;">
            From the TLS terminator on Cloud Run, through every middleware, into the router body, and
            (if the route is a money-mover) into the orchestrator.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="diagram">
          <pre class="mermaid" is:raw>
flowchart TD
    R[HTTPS request<br/>Cloud Run TLS term] --> MW1[RequestIdMiddleware<br/>x-request-id]
    MW1 --> MW2[StructuredLoggingMiddleware]
    MW2 --> MW3[SecurityHeadersMiddleware<br/>CSP / HSTS / Frame-Options]
    MW3 --> MW4[RequestBodyLimitMiddleware]
    MW4 --> MW5[RateLimitMiddleware<br/>Redis token bucket]
    MW5 --> MW6[TapVerificationMiddleware<br/>optional — Visa TAP]
    MW6 --> MW7[X402PaymentMiddleware<br/>optional — 402 gate]
    MW7 --> MW8[UsageMetering + ActivityLogger]
    MW8 --> MW9[CORSMiddleware]
    MW9 --> DEP[require_principal<br/>API key / JWT / session]
    DEP --> ROUTE{Router body}
    ROUTE -->|money-mover| ORCH[PaymentOrchestrator.execute]
    ROUTE -->|read-only| DB[(Neon Postgres)]
    ORCH --> PIPE[PreExecutionPipeline<br/>policy · KYC · mandate · rate · anomaly]
    PIPE --> CHAIN[ChainExecutor → Turnkey MPC → Alchemy RPC]
    CHAIN --> LED[Ledger append + Merkle anchor]
    LED --> RESP[HTTP 2xx / RFC 7807 problem+json]
          </pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Group 1: Auth & Identity -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Group 01</div>
          <h2>Auth &amp; Identity.</h2>
          <p class="text-muted" style="max-width:720px;">
            Principal establishment — how a caller proves they are allowed to address the API at all. Three
            principal types coexist: human users (JWT / session), tenant service accounts (API keys
            <code>sk_live_…</code>), and agents (AGIT identity + signed mandate).
          </p>
        </div>
        <table class="data">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Router</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Auth</th><th>Notable endpoints</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><code>auth.py</code></td>
              <td>Human login, signup, MFA, OAuth, password reset, API-key bootstrap.</td>
              <td>Public + JWT for protected ops</td>
              <td><code>POST /login</code> · <code>POST /signup</code> · <code>POST /refresh</code> · <code>GET /google/callback</code> · <code>POST /mfa/setup</code> · <code>POST /api-keys</code></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>api_keys.py</code></td>
              <td>Tenant API-key CRUD + scoping + hashed storage (SHA-256).</td>
              <td>JWT (tenant admin)</td>
              <td>Create/list/revoke keys; scope by environment (live/test).</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>agent_identity.py</code></td>
              <td>AGIT (Agent Identity and Trust) registration — Ed25519/ECDSA-P256.</td>
              <td>API key</td>
              <td>Register agent identity, rotate keys, attest.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>agent_auth.py</code></td>
              <td>Signed-request auth for agents calling on their own behalf.</td>
              <td>AGIT signature</td>
              <td>Challenge-response + replay cache.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>me.py</code></td>
              <td>Current principal introspection — "whoami" for debugging auth.</td>
              <td>Any</td>
              <td><code>GET /me</code> returns principal type, tenant, scopes.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>email_verification.py</code></td>
              <td>Email confirmation flow for new signups.</td>
              <td>Token link</td>
              <td>Verify, resend.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>credentials.py</code></td>
              <td>Provider credential vault (Turnkey / Stripe / Didit keys per tenant).</td>
              <td>JWT (tenant admin)</td>
              <td>Encrypted at rest; never returned cleartext.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>fides_identity.py</code></td>
              <td>FIDES decentralized trust graph identity lookup.</td>
              <td>API key</td>
              <td>Trust score + attestation chain for an agent.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <!-- Group 2: Wallets & Agents -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Group 02</div>
          <h2>Wallets &amp; Agents.</h2>
          <p class="text-muted" style="max-width:720px;">
            Non-custodial MPC wallets plus the agent records that own them. Wallet-facing endpoints never
            take a private key — signing is deferred to Turnkey (or Fireblocks / Circle) at execution time.
          </p>
        </div>
        <table class="data">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Router</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Auth</th><th>Notable endpoints</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><code>wallets.py</code></td>
              <td>Wallet lifecycle + balances + smart-account upgrade + transfer.</td>
              <td>API key / JWT</td>
              <td><code>POST /wallets</code> · <code>GET /&#123;id&#125;/balance</code> · <code>GET /&#123;id&#125;/balances</code> · <code>POST /&#123;id&#125;/transfer</code> · <code>POST /&#123;id&#125;/freeze</code> · <code>POST /&#123;id&#125;/upgrade-smart-account</code></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>agents.py</code></td>
              <td>Agent CRUD, metadata, owning-tenant linkage.</td>
              <td>API key</td>
              <td>Create agent, attach wallet, assign policy.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>agent_registry.py</code></td>
              <td>Public directory of registered agents for discovery / A2A.</td>
              <td>Mixed</td>
              <td>Search by capability, name, owner.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>agent_heartbeat.py</code></td>
              <td>Liveness signal — stale agents get KYA-suspended.</td>
              <td>AGIT signature</td>
              <td>Periodic ping; last-seen feeds trust score.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>agent_activity.py</code></td>
              <td>Per-agent activity stream (auth events, tx, policy hits).</td>
              <td>API key</td>
              <td>Paginated timeline for dashboard.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>agent_events.py</code></td>
              <td>Emit + query structured agent events (used by KYA &amp; anomaly).</td>
              <td>API key</td>
              <td>Post event; stream by agent_id.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>groups.py</code></td>
              <td>Agent groups — shared budget + policy inheritance.</td>
              <td>API key</td>
              <td>Create group, attach agents, group-level spending cap.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>organizations.py</code></td>
              <td>Tenant (organization) management — users, roles, env scoping.</td>
              <td>JWT (org admin)</td>
              <td>Invite member, switch role, rotate org API keys.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>holds.py</code></td>
              <td>Reserve funds against a wallet for a pending charge.</td>
              <td>API key</td>
              <td>Create / capture / release.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <!-- Group 3: Payments & Mandates -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Group 03</div>
          <h2>Payments &amp; Mandates.</h2>
          <p class="text-muted" style="max-width:720px;">
            The core money-movers. Every route here ultimately calls
            <code>PaymentOrchestrator.execute()</code> — there is no private fast path. A mandate is the
            delegated authority from a principal to an agent; a payment is what happens when that authority
            is exercised.
          </p>
        </div>
        <table class="data">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Router</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Auth</th><th>Notable endpoints</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><code>pay.py</code></td>
              <td>Single-shot agent payment — the flagship <code>sardis.pay()</code> path.</td>
              <td>API key + AGIT</td>
              <td><code>POST /pay</code> — amount, to, reason, optional policy override.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>mandates.py</code></td>
              <td>Spending mandates: create, validate, execute, cancel.</td>
              <td>API key</td>
              <td><code>POST /mandates</code> · <code>POST /&#123;id&#125;/validate</code> · <code>POST /&#123;id&#125;/execute</code> · <code>POST /&#123;id&#125;/cancel</code></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>mandate_delegation.py</code></td>
              <td>Principal → agent delegation chain, sub-delegation with caps.</td>
              <td>Signed mandate</td>
              <td>Issue, revoke, introspect.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>mandate_subscriptions.py</code></td>
              <td>Recurring mandates (subscriptions with budget windows).</td>
              <td>API key</td>
              <td>Start / pause / next-renewal.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>spending_mandates.py</code></td>
              <td>Natural-language spending-mandate creation and enforcement.</td>
              <td>API key</td>
              <td>Parse NL → structured mandate; bind to agent.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>ap2.py</code></td>
              <td>AP2 (Agent Payment Protocol) mandate-chain verification + execute.</td>
              <td>AP2 signed chain</td>
              <td><code>POST /ap2/payments/execute</code> — verifies Intent→Cart→Payment.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>batch_payments.py</code></td>
              <td>Submit many payments in a single request; per-item policy result.</td>
              <td>API key</td>
              <td>Atomic batch · per-item settle.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>streaming_payments.py</code></td>
              <td>Micropayment streams (per-second / per-token rates).</td>
              <td>API key</td>
              <td>Open stream, tick, close.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>payments_refund.py</code></td>
              <td>Initiate refunds through Circle RefundProtocol + PSP rails.</td>
              <td>API key</td>
              <td>Full / partial / dispute-linked.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>subscriptions.py</code></td>
              <td>Merchant subscription billing (Polar adapter).</td>
              <td>API key</td>
              <td>Plan CRUD, usage roll-up.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>mpp.py</code></td>
              <td>Stripe Merchant Payment Protocol (MPP) integration for Tempo mainnet.</td>
              <td>API key</td>
              <td>MPP quote → pay → receipt.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>swap.py</code></td>
              <td>Token swaps via DEX router (Tempo, Base).</td>
              <td>API key</td>
              <td>Quote, execute, slippage-protect.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>payment_objects.py</code></td>
              <td>Canonical payment object retrieval (ID → full record + state machine).</td>
              <td>API key</td>
              <td>Read by id, filter by status.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <!-- Group 4: Policy & Compliance -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Group 04</div>
          <h2>Policy &amp; Compliance.</h2>
          <p class="text-muted" style="max-width:720px;">
            The gate. Natural-language policies in, structured enforcement out. KYC via Didit, sanctions via
            Elliptic, KYA (Know Your Agent) implemented internally. Every rejection is audited with a reason
            code.
          </p>
        </div>
        <table class="data">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Router</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Auth</th><th>Notable endpoints</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><code>policies.py</code></td>
              <td>Spending policy CRUD, preview, apply, history, recommendations.</td>
              <td>API key (+ MPP gate on parse/check)</td>
              <td><code>POST /parse</code> · <code>POST /preview</code> · <code>POST /apply</code> · <code>POST /check</code> · <code>GET /templates</code> · <code>GET /&#123;agent&#125;/history</code></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>policy_analytics.py</code></td>
              <td>Aggregate policy-decision metrics (allow rate, top denied reason codes).</td>
              <td>JWT</td>
              <td>Trend by agent, by reason.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>policy_simulation.py</code></td>
              <td>Dry-run a candidate policy against historical traffic.</td>
              <td>JWT</td>
              <td>Replay window, impact report.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>fallback_policies.py</code></td>
              <td>Safety-net policies applied when a primary policy errors.</td>
              <td>JWT</td>
              <td>Global deny-cap, max-amount backstop.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>approvals.py</code> · <code>approval_config.py</code></td>
              <td>Human-in-the-loop approval queue for over-threshold agent requests.</td>
              <td>JWT</td>
              <td>Create request, approve / reject, notify via webhook.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>compliance.py</code></td>
              <td>KYC verify, KYA register/check/suspend, sanctions screen.</td>
              <td>JWT / API key</td>
              <td><code>POST /kyc/verify</code> · <code>GET /kyc/&#123;agent&#125;</code> · <code>POST /kya/register</code> · <code>POST /sanctions/screen</code> · <code>POST /sanctions/block</code></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>kyc_onboarding.py</code></td>
              <td>Didit session bootstrap → webhook → <code>sk_live_</code> issuance.</td>
              <td>JWT</td>
              <td><code>POST /kyc/initiate</code>.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>compliance_export.py</code></td>
              <td>Regulated evidence bundles (PDF + JSON + Merkle proof).</td>
              <td>JWT (admin)</td>
              <td>Export by date range / agent.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>trust.py</code></td>
              <td>FIDES trust-graph mutation (upvote, revoke, peer-attest).</td>
              <td>AGIT signature</td>
              <td>Graph ops + local trust score.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>anomaly.py</code></td>
              <td>Anomaly detector scoring + rule tuning.</td>
              <td>JWT</td>
              <td>Score a request, tune threshold.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>erc8183.py</code></td>
              <td>ERC-8183 policy-guard hooks for on-chain enforcement.</td>
              <td>API key</td>
              <td>Guard check, USDC cap, fee cap.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>guardrails</code> (via <code>sardis-guardrails</code>)</td>
              <td>Agent guardrail presets referenced from <code>policies.py</code>.</td>
              <td>API key</td>
              <td>Template by persona (buyer, trader, ops).</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <!-- Group 5: Checkout & Merchant -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Group 05</div>
          <h2>Checkout &amp; Merchant.</h2>
          <p class="text-muted" style="max-width:720px;">
            "Pay with Sardis" — the consumer-facing checkout. Public endpoints auth by <code>client_secret</code>
            (never session id); merchant management endpoints auth by <code>require_principal</code>.
            Hardened against double-pay via <code>SELECT … FOR UPDATE NOWAIT</code> and DB-unique
            idempotency keys.
          </p>
        </div>
        <table class="data">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Router</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Auth</th><th>Notable endpoints</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><code>checkout.py</code></td>
              <td>Low-level checkout object CRUD + public status read.</td>
              <td>Public (client_secret) / API key</td>
              <td><code>POST /checkout</code> · <code>GET /&#123;id&#125;</code> · <code>GET /payment-methods</code></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>merchant_checkout.py</code></td>
              <td>Merchant-scoped checkout sessions, SSE stream, links.</td>
              <td>Merchant API key / public link</td>
              <td>Create session, <code>/stream</code> SSE, reusable checkout link, external-wallet confirm.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>checkout_controls.py</code></td>
              <td>Per-merchant checkout controls (min/max amount, allowed tokens).</td>
              <td>Merchant JWT</td>
              <td>Upsert controls.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>merchants.py</code></td>
              <td>Merchant account CRUD, settlement address, embed_origin.</td>
              <td>JWT</td>
              <td>Create merchant, rotate keys.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><code>secure_checkout.py</code></td>
              <td>Step-up auth + SCA-style challenges for high-value sessions.</td>
              <td>Session token</td>
              <td>Start challenge, verify.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
