      <!-- Error model -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Contract</div>
          <h2>Error model — RFC 7807 problem+json.</h2>
          <p class="text-muted" style="max-width:720px;">
            Every non-2xx response conforms to <a href="https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7807" target="_blank" rel="noopener">RFC 7807</a>.
            Clients key off <code>type</code> (stable URI) and <code>code</code> (enum) — not the HTTP
            status alone, and definitely not the <code>title</code> string.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-2">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">Shape</div>
            <div class="card-description">
              Every error carries: <code>type</code> (URI ref), <code>title</code> (short human), <code>status</code>
              (HTTP code), <code>detail</code> (human detail), <code>code</code> (machine enum),
              <code>request_id</code> (for grep'ing logs), and when applicable <code>reason_code</code>
              (policy engine) or <code>retry_after</code> (rate limit).
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">Categories</div>
            <dl class="defs">
              <dt><code>400</code> validation_error</dt><dd>Pydantic schema mismatch — array of field errors in <code>errors[]</code>.</dd>
              <dt><code>401</code> auth_required</dt><dd>Missing / malformed principal. <code>WWW-Authenticate</code> set.</dd>
              <dt><code>403</code> policy_denied</dt><dd>Pre-execution pipeline rejection. <code>reason_code</code> names the gate.</dd>
              <dt><code>409</code> conflict</dt><dd>Idempotency collision or state-machine violation.</dd>
              <dt><code>422</code> mandate_invalid</dt><dd>AP2 / TAP / mandate chain verification failed.</dd>
              <dt><code>429</code> rate_limited</dt><dd>Redis token-bucket refusal. <code>retry_after</code> in seconds.</dd>
              <dt><code>500</code> internal</dt><dd>Unclassified — always carries <code>request_id</code>.</dd>
              <dt><code>503</code> unavailable</dt><dd>Dependency fail-closed (Redis, KYA, FIDES).</dd>
            </dl>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

